{
  "text": "The main endpoint was the rate of AL. AL was suspected following clinical presentation and findings from physical examination. The diagnosis was confirmed using contrast-enhanced computed tomography, endoscopic examination, or during surgery. The extent of AL was characterized using the grading system proposed by Rahbari et al. [CITATION_1] . According to this grading system, AL requiring no therapeutic intervention is classified as grade A and grade B leakages are managed via endoscopic, sonographic, or radiologic intervention, while grade C leakages warrant surgical revision.",
